1. The serum IL-10 in group A was measured.
2. The serum IL-10 in group C was measured.
3. The serum IL-10 level in group A was higher than in group C.
4. The difference in serum IL-10 levels between group A and group C was statistically significant (P<0.01).
5. The serum E-selectin levels in group A were measured.
6. The serum E-selectin levels in group C were measured.
7. The serum E-selectin levels in group A and group C were compared.
8. There was no significant difference in serum E-selectin levels between group A and group C (P>0.05).
